# Product Requirements Document (PRD)

## 1. Product Overview

**Product Name:** (Working Name)

**Product Type:** Enterprise EdTech + Professional Network + Recruitment Platform

**Vision:**
Create a unified, scalable SaaS platform that fuses the *professional identity and networking strengths of LinkedIn* with the *structured learning and certification depth of Udemy* — while remaining original, skills-first, and enterprise-focused.

The platform is not a clone of LinkedIn or Udemy. Instead, it re-centers the experience around **verified skills, learning-to-hiring flow, and enterprise recruitment execution**.

---

## 2. Target Users & Personas

### Learners / Professionals

* Students
* Early-career professionals
* Skilled workers
* Career switchers

### Employers / Recruiters

* HR managers
* Recruiters
* Hiring managers

### Instructors / Organizations

* Training providers
* Enterprises
* Educational institutions

### Platform Admins

* System administrators
* Content moderators

---

## 3. Core Use Cases

### Learner

* Create a professional profile
* Enroll in courses and skill paths
* Earn certificates
* Build a verified skill-based profile
* Apply for jobs using profile
* Participate in professional discussions

### Recruiter

* Post jobs
* View candidate profiles
* Run assessments
* Schedule interviews
* Manage hiring pipeline

### Instructor / Organization

* Publish courses
* Track learner progress
* Issue certificates

---

## 4. Functional Requirements

### 4.1 Authentication & Access

* Login / Signup (email, OAuth-ready)
* Role-based access control
* Secure session handling

---

### 4.2 User Profile (LinkedIn-style)

* Profile photo
* Name & professional headline
* About section
* Skills list
* Education history
* Work experience
* Certifications (auto-added from completed courses)
* Edit profile
* Public / private visibility controls

---

### 4.3 Social Feed

* Post creation (text, links)
* Feed cards
* Like, comment, share
* Follow users
* Right sidebar:

  * Trending courses
  * Trending jobs

---

### 4.4 Learning Management (EdTech)

* Course catalog
* Course cards
* Skill paths
* Course progress tracking
* Assessments & quizzes
* Certificates & badge UI
* Learning dashboard

---

### 4.5 Job Listings

* Job cards
* Job search & filters:

  * Role
  * Location
  * Remote
* Apply using profile
* Company preview card

---

### 4.6 Recruitment Dashboard (HR CRM)

* Candidate pipeline stages:

  * Applied
  * Test
  * Interview
  * Hired
* Candidate list & filtering
* Candidate profile modal
* Interview scheduling calendar
* Assessment & test results view

---

### 4.7 Interview Room

* In-app video call
* Candidate video panel
* Interviewer video panel
* Coding test / task panel
* Interview notes
* Timer & call controls

---

## 5. UI / UX Requirements

### Design Style

* Clean, corporate, minimal
* White background
* Soft blue accents
* Card-based layout
* Rounded corners
* Subtle shadows
* Sans-serif typography (Inter / Roboto style)

### Layout

* Desktop-first
* Fully responsive

### Navigation

* Top navigation bar:

  * Home
  * Learning
  * Jobs
  * Network
  * Messages
  * Profile
* Left sidebar for dashboards

### Overall Feel

* Trustworthy
* Professional
* Scalable enterprise SaaS
* LinkedIn-inspired but distinct

---

## 6. Non-Functional Requirements

### Performance

* Fast page load (<2s)
* Support high concurrent users

### Security

* Secure authentication
* Role-based permissions
* Data encryption

### Scalability

* Multi-tenant ready
* Modular architecture

### Accessibility

* WCAG-compliant UI

---

## 7. Success Metrics (KPIs)

* User signups
* Course completion rate
